article.headline: Lehigh 65, Albany, N.Y. 64
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Zahir Carrington grabbed a rebound and dropped in a layup with three seconds left to lead Lehigh to a 65-64 victory over Albany, N.Y., on Monday night. Carrington, who finished with six points, grabbed the rebound of Bob Keefer's missed jumper and misfired with a jumper before getting his own rebound and hitting the game-winning basket. A basket by Tim Ambrose had given Albany a 64-63 lead with 41 seconds left. Marquis Hall scored 23 points, and Michael Ojo added 12 for Lehigh (6-3), which overcame 9-for-23 shooting in the first half with 15-for-28 sniping in the second half. Will Harris scored 21 points and Ambrose finished with 17 for Albany (5-4), which shot 23-for-61 (38 percent) in the loss.
